Yeah, if your doing small stuff and happen to have an EPROM programmer, I'd just make a NROM cart for experiments. Not expensive if you have a programmer or get one cheap, and if you need bigger carts, there's lots of donors out there. (NOT CRYSTALIS! <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />)<br /><br /><br />I made alot (3 or 4) 16K and 32K carts, they work fine for now....but I need to make a 512K cart soon for....."other stuff" <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt=":roll:" title="Rolling Eyes" /><br /><br /><br />but yeah if you want something that works on nearly everything and have $150 to spare, PowerPak is probably better for 3x the cost, ALOT less time consuming, it's worth it....<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4311">3gengames</a> — Thu Oct 14, 2010 1:29 pm</p><hr />
